{
  "texts": [
    "In this sense, IVG relies on the foundation established by DSG.",
    "The grounded understanding of MinSet words enables individuals to grasp more complex concepts that are defined or described using these foundational words.",
    "SH: DSG is based on learning to detect the sensorimotor features that distinguish members from nonmembers of a category directly, using something like neural nets to detect and abstract those sensorimotor features.",
    "IVG does not use the distinguishing sensorimotor features themselves, but their names and verbal descriptions.",
    "These feature-names need to have already been grounded (directly or indirectly) in the head of the human learner to allow the teacher's verbal description to be understood by the learner, empowering the names and descriptions to ground (indirectly), in the head of the learner, the new category of which they are the features."
  ]
}